## Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.12+
- API keys for your chosen LLM provider (see `.env.example`)

### Setup

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone {{ repo_url | default("<repo-url>") }}
cd {{ repo_dir | default(pipeline_name) }}

# Configure environment
cp .env.example .env
# Fill in your API keys in .env

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements-runtime.txt
```

### Run

```bash
# Preview the pipeline DAG (no API calls, no cost)
python3 -m lib.runner --pipeline pipelines/{{ version | default("v1") }}.json --dry-run

# Execute the full pipeline
python3 -m lib.runner --pipeline pipelines/{{ version | default("v1") }}.json --data-dir data/

# Resume from a checkpoint or after failure
python3 -m lib.runner --pipeline pipelines/{{ version | default("v1") }}.json --run-id <run-id> --resume
```

### Output

Outputs are written to `workspace/outputs/runs/{run_id}/`:

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `manifest.json` | Run metadata (pipeline version, timestamps, config) |
| `ledger.jsonl` | Append-only event stream for every step transition |
| `run_state.json` | Per-step status, timing, and error details |
| `{{ final_output | default("final_report.json") }}` | **The final deliverable** |

